post_text: We were thrilled to have School District 64 so well represented during a program honoring former U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton today. The Park Ridge Historical Society invited 100 students from Lincoln Middle School, 100 from Emerson Middle School and Girl Scouts from Field Elementary to a program featuring Clinton at the Pickwick Theater. Secretary Clinton grew up in Park Ridge and attended Field School. Field's Learning Resource Center was named in her honor in 2016.

post_text:
Park Ridge-Niles School District 64 extends an invitation to all D64 residents to share your thoughts as we search for our next Superintendent of Schools. Please take this very brief online survey before Jan. 31 about our District’s strengths and challenges, and the characteristics our next leader should possess.

Or, consider attending one of the open forums from 7:00-7:45 p.m. on Tuesday, January 29 (Roosevelt School (auditorium), 1001 S. Fairview, Park Ridge) or Wednesday, January 30 (Lincoln Middle School (Learning Resource Center), 200 S. Lincoln, Park Ridge). See more information about the search here.

http://www.d64.org/boe/superintendent-search-2018-19

Your ideas will shape a New Superintendent Profile to guide the Board in its selection process. Thank you for participating!

post_text:
District 64 is inviting all community members to participate in a survey focused on our Middle School Mission. The survey will be conducted as a Thoughtexchange online conversation open through Tuesday, November 14.

Enter the D64 conversation for community members here:
https://my.thoughtexchange.com/#843216117/hub

We want to hear from you about how we are fulfilling our Middle School mission and your ideas for improvement, and other things you'd like to see to improve the middle school experience for students in the future.

D64 initiated a Middle School Review this fall as part of the 2020 Vision Strategic Plan. D64 last initiated a middle school review back in 2006 and previously in 1993. The Thoughtexchange will help inform the Review Committee's work and the administration's spring recommendation to the Board of Education.

Please join the conversation!

post_text: Roosevelt Tiger families - please check out these important winter school closing guidelines.
shared_text:
D64.ORG
www.d64.org

District 64 Park Ridge-Niles
November 28, 2016 at 10:22 AM ·

With December's colder weather just ahead, take a minute to review District 64's winter closing guidelines for 2016-17. Our guidelines focus on wind chill and use the National Weather Service distinctions between an advisory and a warning (among other factors) when considering whether schools will be closed. As always, our first priority is the safety of students and staff. View the guidelines here: http://www.d64.org/communications/documents/Winterflyer2016.pdf

post_text: Holiday Food Baskets - we invite your support! Help us provide holiday food baskets for District 64 families in need! Last year, 35 families from District 64 were aided, thanks to the efforts of the Park Ridge Kiwanis Club. Help us serve even more families this holiday season! Simply dine at Harp & Fiddle, 110 Main St., Park Ridge, on Wednesday, November 9 from 4 p.m. - 10 p.m., and tell your server you're with the Kiwanis/D64 benefit. 20% of your total bill will be donated to this great cause! Read more here: http://www.d64.org/news/Join-us-on-Nov-9-for-holiday-basket-fundraiser-for-District-64-families.cfm?grp_id=16593
